						               													<description>The Music Game: Primary (Level A) is a fun board game for children that promotes a recognition and understanding of the basics of music. The Primary Music Game's easy and exciting approach encourages group participation and provides opportunities for creative musical expression. Charming drawings of animals and cartoon characters introduce the elements of music as a happy experience, which stimulates and develops the child's musical growth. Children learn music through fun activities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Teachers/parents and children do not need any musical knowledge to play this game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Used in the classroom or at home. The Primary Music Game makes an excellent teaching aid and can be adapted to any music program. Teachers/parents using this game will also find that children can learn music at their own pace.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECT OF THE GAME:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the first group or child to reach the Finish position on the far right side of the game board. Players advance their coloured marker clips from left to right along the white and coloured piano keys (not the black ones) by rolling the die, and correctly responding to the Musical Category Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE MUSICAL CATEGORIES:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1: Musical Notes&amp;#10;2: Musical Keys&amp;#10;3: Musical Rhythm&amp;#10;4: Musical Signs&amp;#10;5: Musical Words&amp;#10;6: Music Makers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the rulebook&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
